paepae
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:(also pae) the threshold beam of a meeting house; a bench to seat orators at the front of a meeting house.
Origin:Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: The beam forming a bench at the threshold of a meeting house.
